My take is different on this.  I agree with Ted in that I believe that 
Moira&#39;s pronunciation is in the minority, but so what?  I say jettison 
the rule and stick with phonemic writing.  It causes me no difficulty to 
read Moira&#39;s QS with &quot;It&quot; at the end of words as opposed to &quot;Eat.&quot;  She 
can spell it the way she wants, and I can spell it with &quot;Eat.&quot; way. 

I&#39;ve been reading the QS news with some peculiar spellings such as 
&quot;jurists&quot; written as &quot;juris&quot;  I want to know what&#39;s up with that?  Is 
that really in the CMU dictionary or is that some peculiarity of the 
tranliteration program Paul wrote?  The closest dictionary to hand 
happens to be a Funk & Wagnall&#39;s.  The pronunciation shows a &quot;t&quot; at the 
end of the word.

Paige

